modules.description: Provides functions to convert rawlink interfaces into MirageOS flow types, enabling network data processing. Works with rawlink device handles and flow-based data structures. Used to integrate low-level network interfaces with higher-level MirageOS networking stacks for packet transmission and reception.

Provides functions to read from and write to network flows using buffer structures, with error handling for read and write operations. Operates on `flow` handles and `buffer` objects representing data chunks, supporting both single and vectorized writes. Used to manage reliable data transmission over raw network links, including proper closure and error reporting.
